properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 4 at 3:13AM HST until January 7 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, east winds 25 to 30 kt with
and seas 7 to 11 feet. For the Gale Watch, east winds to 35 kt
and seas 8 to 14 feet possible.

* WHERE...Pailolo Channel and Alenuihaha Channel.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 6 AM HST Sunday.
For the Gale Watch, from Sunday morning through Tuesday
afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Watch is issued when the risk of gale force winds of 34 to
47 knots has significantly increased but the specific timing
and/or location is still uncertain. It is intended to provide
additional lead time for mariners who may wish to consider
altering their plans.
